descriptions: Details about authentication obtained during the password reset flow.
event.authentication.title: EventAuthentication

descriptions: An object containing information that describes the authorization granted to the user logging in.
event.authorization.title: EventAuthorization

descriptions: An array containing the names of the user's assigned roles.
event.authorization.roles.title: EventAuthorizationRoles

descriptions:
Information about the Client with which the password reset
          transaction was initiated.
event.client.title: EventClient

descriptions: The client id of the application the user is logging in to.
event.client.client_id.title: EventClientClient_id

descriptions: An object for holding other application properties.
event.client.metadata.title: EventClientMetadata

descriptions: The name of the application (as defined in the Dashboard).
event.client.name.title: EventClientName

descriptions: Details about the connection used to authenticate the user.
event.connection.title: EventConnection

descriptions: The connection's unique identifier.
event.connection.id.title: EventConnectionId

descriptions: Metadata associated with the connection.
event.connection.metadata.title: EventConnectionMetadata

descriptions:
The name of the connection used to authenticate the user (such as
              twitter or example-g-suite-domain).
event.connection.name.title: EventConnectionName

descriptions:
The type of connection.
            
              For social connections,
                event.connection.strategy === event.connection.name.
               For enterprise connections, the strategy is
              waad (Windows Azure AD), ad (Active Directory/LDAP), auth0 (database connections), and so
                on.
event.connection.strategy.title: EventConnectionStrategy

descriptions:
Details about the Organization associated with the current
          transaction.
event.organization.title: EventOrganization

descriptions: The friendly name of the Organization.
event.organization.display_name.title: EventOrganizationDisplay_name

descriptions: The Organization identifier.
event.organization.id.title: EventOrganizationId

descriptions: Metadata associated with the Organization.
event.organization.metadata.title: EventOrganizationMetadata

descriptions: The name of the Organization.
event.organization.name.title: EventOrganizationName

descriptions: Details about the request that initiated the transaction.
event.request.title: EventRequest

descriptions:
The body of the POST request. This data is only available
              during refresh token and Client Credential Exchange flows.
event.request.body.title: EventRequestBody

descriptions:
The hostname used for the authentication
              flow.
event.request.hostname.title: EventRequestHostname

descriptions: The originating IP address of the request.
event.request.ip.title: EventRequestIp

descriptions: The language requested by the browser.
event.request.language.title: EventRequestLanguage

descriptions: The HTTP method used for the request.
event.request.method.title: EventRequestMethod

descriptions:
The query string parameters sent to the authorization
              request.
event.request.query.title: EventRequestQuery

descriptions:
The value of the User-Agent header received when
              initiating the transaction.
event.request.user_agent.title: EventRequestUser_agent

descriptions: Login statistics for the current user.
event.stats.title: EventStats

descriptions: The number of times the user has logged in.
event.stats.logins_count.title: EventStatsLogins_count

descriptions: Details about the tenant associated with the current transaction.
event.tenant.title: EventTenant

descriptions: The name of the tenant.
event.tenant.id.title: EventTenantId

descriptions: Details about the current transaction.
event.transaction.title: EventTransaction

descriptions:
The locale to use for this transaction as determined by
              comparing the browser's requested languages to the tenant's
              language settings.
event.transaction.locale.title: EventTransactionLocale

about the login identifier the end-user might use when logging in, if necessary.
event.transaction.login_hint.title: EventTransactionLogin_hint

descriptions:
An opaque, arbitrary alphanumeric string your app adds to the initial request that Auth0 includes when redirecting back to your
              application.
event.transaction.state.title: EventTransactionState

descriptions:
The ui_locales provided in the original authentication
              request.
event.transaction.ui_locales.title: EventTransactionUi_locales

descriptions: An object describing the user associated with the current transaction.
event.user.title: EventUser

descriptions:
Custom fields that store info about a user that influences the
              user's access, such as support plan, security roles, or access
              control groups.
event.user.app_metadata.title: EventUserApp_metadata

descriptions:
Timestamp indicating when the user profile was first
              created.
event.user.created_at.title: EventUserCreated_at

descriptions: (unique) User's email address.
event.user.email.title: EventUserEmail

descriptions:
Indicates whether the user has verified their email
              address.
event.user.email_verified.title: EventUserEmail_verified

descriptions: User's family name.
event.user.family_name.title: EventUserFamily_name

descriptions: User's given name.
event.user.given_name.title: EventUserGiven_name

descriptions:
Timestamp indicating the last time the user's password was
              updated. This field does not exist at user creation. This
              property is only available for Database connections.
event.user.last_password_reset.title: EventUserLast_password_reset

descriptions: User's full name.
event.user.name.title: EventUserName

descriptions: User's nickname.
event.user.nickname.title: EventUserNickname

descriptions:
User's phone number. Only valid for users with SMS
              connections.
event.user.phone_number.title: EventUserPhone_number

descriptions: Indicates whether the user has verified their phone number. Only valid for users with SMS connections.
event.user.phone_verified.title: EventUserPhone_verified

descriptions:
URL pointing to the
              user's profile picture.
event.user.picture.title: EventUserPicture

descriptions:
Timestamp indicating when the user's profile was last
              updated.
event.user.updated_at.title: EventUserUpdated_at

descriptions: (unique) User's unique identifier.
event.user.user_id.title: EventUserUser_id

descriptions: Custom fields that store user information that does not impact their level of access, such as work address, home address, or user preferences.
event.user.user_metadata.title: EventUserUser_metadata

descriptions: (unique) User's username.
event.user.username.title: EventUserUsername
